        @Since(value="7.0")
public Node(Long nodeID,
          Long associatedMasterServiceID,
          Long associatedFServiceID,
          String fibreChannelTargetPortGroup,

          Platform platformInfo,
          String softwareVersion,
          String cip,

          String mip,
          String mipi,
          String sip,
          String sipi,
          UUID uuid,
          Map<String,Object> attributes)
        A node refers to an individual machine in a cluster. Each active node hosts a master service, which is responsible for managing the drives and other services on its node. After a node is made active, its drives will become available for addition to the cluster.
        Parameters:
        nodeID - [required] The unique identifier for this node.
        associatedMasterServiceID - [required] The master service responsible for controlling other services on this node.
        associatedFServiceID - [required]
        fibreChannelTargetPortGroup - [required]
        name - [required]
        platformInfo - [required] Information about the platform this node is.
        softwareVersion - [required] The version of SolidFire software this node is currently running.
        cip - [required] IP address used for both intra- and inter-cluster communication.
        cipi - [required] The machine's name for the "cip" interface.
        mip - [required] IP address used for cluster management (hosting the API and web site).
        mipi - [required] The machine's name for the "mip" interface.
        sip - [required] IP address used for iSCSI traffic.
        sipi - [required] The machine's name for the "sip" interface.
        uuid - [required] UUID of node.
        attributes - [required]
        Since:
        7.0
